In response to this unprecedented crisis, California Association of Realtors, which I am a member of are pleased to a nounce a new form release‚Äîcalled the Coronavirus Addendum/Amendment (Form CVA). It is already available for use in my legal forms for all of my real estate transactions. The form provides that when circumstances related to the coronavirus are affecting the closing date, the Buyer and Seller agree to extend escrow for a default of 30 days. There is also an optional clause where the buyer and seller can mutually agree to cancel the Agreement and an additional optional clause where the buyer or seller can cancel even after removing the loan contingency if inability to fund is caused by Covid-19 related loss of income. This helps create a transaction all parties are content to move forward in. It is business as usual for all of us Realtors and Lenders and I am glad to help! The idea of a city in California taking an anti-gun stand at any given opportunity. We‚Äôve seen it through countless bits of legislation at the state and local levels of California‚Äôs government. They don‚Äôt like guns, despite the massive increase in gun ownership in recent days.

For Fresno city officials, though, the COVID-19 virus was just too good of a crisis to allow it to go to waste.

The City of Fresno has now declared a ‚Äústate of emergency‚Äù, and doing so grants the city wide-ranging powers under its ‚ÄúEmergency Services Ordinance‚Äù. Fox26 News asked for and got a copy of the full ordinance. Among other things, after an emergency declaration, it allows the city to:

1. Suspend the sale of firearms and ammo.

2. Suspend the sale of alcohol.

3. Order a general curfew.

4. Order the closing of all taverns.

5. Order a price or rate freeze on consumer goods and on hotels if lodging is limited.

7. Order a halt to gasoline sales, except as fuel pumped into vehicles‚Äô gasoline tanks.

8. Order the closing of any business where crowds ‚Äútend to gather‚Äù, including theaters, amusement areas, gyms, stadiums, etc.

Fox26 News reached out to the City Government to ask if the ordinance has been challenged in court, or if it has survived a legal challenge. Nobody was available to comment at the time of this writing. We will continue to ask for comment.

During these unsettling times, we are reminded of how important it is to take care of ourselves and each other. My good friends @gatorcases , are privileged to see how powerful music can be in promoting health, well-being and connections with others. We may not be able to go to shows or events, but we can still enjoy the music. Our music community has been hit hard and we want to do our part to help our fans and community feel good and stay connected, even if we need to be separated. Here‚Äôs a view of my humble little recording studio and a snippet of a song that I song that I wrote for my wife @originally_khaatia about that positive feeling I got when I would pick her up in the morning to take her to work. I was living outta my car at the time and she was always a sight for sore and tired eyes. Feeling so thankful to have a roof over our heads now and I can focus on making music! Shout out to @gatorcases @levysmusic for supporting musicians around the world. Tag @gatorcases ‚Äì they‚Äôre taking requests. insta_description:
I'm lucky to spend the next month and a half making collections of the stunning genus, Calochortus (Liliaceae), taking social distancing to the most lovely and mountainous extreme that someone like John Muir would have been proud of. My lab at @uwbotany in collaboration with a lab at @cornelluniversity are working on a grant from the @nsfgov to study the evolution of this wonderful genus. I'll start by making collections of 4 target species all thought to be most closely related, yet show striking morphological differences in floral form, 2 are 'cat's ears' as seen here, and two are 'fairly lanterns' that never fully open. By studying my collections we are hoping to work out which form evolved first and which genes are turned on and off during bud development to produce the two forms. Later I will be collecting many more of the ~70 species to build a phylogenetic tree for the genus which we will use to map historical patterns of biogeography and trait evolution onto the group. 
Pictured here are C. monophyllus (VU) in yellow, C. tolmiei in white, and some snow that the Sierra Mountains just got this weekend after the driest February in history.

insta_description: Looking for a place to be socially distant? About a month ago we visited Death Valley and absolutely loved it. Holding numerous records (flattest, lowest, hottest, etc.), spring is one of the best times to visit the park. Geographically, hiking through Badwater Basin was such a unique experience - the white on the ground isn‚Äôt sand, but salt. The crystals are remarkably hard, and the whole world sparkles under the sun. The experience is like hiking on the surface of a giant quartz crystal. The hike to cross the basin is about six miles one way, but you need only head out about three miles to completely lose sight of people. Bring PLENTY of water - Death Valley earns its name in all weather ;) #deathvalley #deathvalleynationalpark #deathvalleynps #badwaterbasin #badwater #desert #desertlife #deserthiking #deserthike #california #nationalpark #takeahike #gooutside #adventure #thegreatoutdoors #hikes

insta_description:
Waning Crescent Moon.
GROUNDING, with my prayerüïØCreating a connection with you, woven in words as love letters is my humble grounding prayer today. üïØPrayers for you & your loved ones.

Hello my love, how are you?
May I please offer this space for you to check in?
I would absolutely love to hear how you‚Äôre holding up. Got any  coping tips? Need some coping tips? Please feel free to comment here. üïØPrayers for calm & kind space.

On this Wednesday ruled by Mercury the planet of communication, element of air, I am happy to share with you a few spoonfuls of lovin‚Äô.
My little family & big family are all physically well so far. Here in Southern California we are preparing for high winds this afternoon & a rainstorm tomorrow (Thursday). üïØPrayers for houseless folx.

It has been a rollercoaster of rapid adjustment for my 2 teenagers.  Visual communications in youth social media has been less smooth than I dreamed. There is a huge variety of factors that swirl through the air where we live and not all of the teenagers in their life have been able or willing to isolate.
It‚Äôs made it a whole lot more pressure in the already super charged atmosphere of being in a teenage body. üïØPrayers for teenagers.

My sweetheart is working triple overtime as their work is servicing medical equipment & in my lifelong home in Orange County it is all hands on deck supporting hospitals. üïØPrayers for all folks in the MEDICAL FEILD.

Many of you have checked on Mama & Pops (85 & 81).Thank you for that! They are cozy & well just 2 miles from me. They live in a 55+ condo complex in a part of town with predominantly elderly folks. The collective field of memory keepers there is so special & important. üïØPrayers for elders.

We are creating a framework based on pleasure as best we can, in our isolation. Today that means sanitizing our home by cycling through a mountain of laundry and finishing my VLOG for my YouTube channel. üïØPrayers for Witches. 
Sending you Love&Magick,
Angela x.
View of Saddleback Mountain Orange County California 2020.
Swipe for my a view of my folks Altar today. üïØprayers for Mama & Pops

1. I can hide how badly I need my Botox touched up

2. I can avoid people no questions asked while I let my haircut grow out

3. No one thinks I‚Äôm a lazy piece of shit for laying in bed with my cat all day

4. I‚Äôm learning how creative I can be when coming up with reasons as to why I need to Zoom or FaceTime someone RIGHT NOW

5. My house has never been cleaner

6. I‚Äôve gotten so good at not snacking, courtesy of there literally being none of my regular snack foods available

7. I‚Äôm gonna get so tan cause of all the time I get to spend laying outside all day long now

8. I‚Äôve never had so many photos of myself to choose from when posting on IG

I hope y‚Äôall can sense my sarcasm woven into this listüòÇ but why not?

Life is too short to be taken so seriously. You can always put a positive spin on anything, even if it‚Äôs not the ideal scenario and dripping in sarcasm.

So just have some fucking fun with it.

This has been a hard few weeks & life in #california continues to get harder due to #covid19.....
‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢
On Monday, a mandate came out for 6 #bayarea counties to implement #shelterinplace policies for their residents. That means that we must stay in our homes, practicing #socialdistancing, at all times except for a few approved activities including going to the grocery store, medical appointments, & exercise (+ a few more but you get the idea). Everything is closed except for businesses that are deemed ‚Äúessential‚Äù or who can provide delivery or takeout options.
‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢
I have #depression & #anxiety. There have been moments in the last few days where I have become panicked, angry, frustrated, scared, deeply sad, & at times, only able to get out of bed when coaxed by the husband. ‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢
I am having all of these emotions & they are valid. If you are having these feelings, you are not alone. This is a crazy, never-before-seen, changing-everyday time. Yet, I am still going to show up to work. I am still going to be an incredible #nurse for my patients & colleagues. I am going to continue to support #nurses & #futurenurses every day through my work with @newthingnurse, @enaorg, @aacn, & all the amazing online nurse groups on social media. üíØ
‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢
Despite everything, I am still hopeful. What makes me hopeful is knowing that there are so many incredibly passionate, smart, talented #healthcare professionals & supporters who are working together to overcome the COVID19 challenge. I see you online in photos. I speak to you everyday via messenger, phone, text, email. I work with you at the bedside. I have surrounded myself with all of you + my family & friends. Together, we will get through this. That is how I am coping. üíõüíõüíõüíõüíõüíõüíõüíõüíõ
Much love to each of you. Be safe. Protect yourself & your patients. Reach out for whatever you need. Together, we got this. üíõ @newthingnurse #coronavirus #corona #nursestrong #strongertogether #mentalhealth

Ok so I more than understand this critical time, we are forever haunted by the media reports. They do an excellent job of making us all go a little nuts... Ok fine, We practices sanitizing, reduce going out in public, watch our health symptoms and everything we are supposed to do.... And still we are unsure. 
What about when a job that you have just up and decides to tell you, you don't have a job for 2 weeks because you traveled? What about someone who went up North to visit family, or down south for vacation, and so many more options.... How does any employer know where any of it's employees have been, if they are infected, or exposed?

So you send them home with no pay, maybe, just maybe unemployment, how are they supposed to live and pay bills? 
If you as an employer can randomly decide who can work and who can't then pay your damn employees full pay, and/or pay for them to be tested. 
Come on let's protect our workforce not pick and choose who to temporarily let go!

insta_description:
Dear Valued Patient,

The health and safety of the patients and staff of Dr. Salma Aziz are of primary importance. Like the rest of the world, we continue to monitor the COVID-19 developments. Following guidelines set forth from the Centers for Disease Control (CDC) and World Health Organization (WHO), we are confident in the precautionary measures and response plans we have established.

At this time, our clinics are operating as normal. We have reviewed our clinic continuity plans and do not anticipate any scenario that would impair our ability to treat our patients. While we do not believe panic is in any way warranted, we do wish to practice community-conscious medicine and protect each other and our patients from this virus (as well as flu or any other communicable infectious disease). We are asking all patients that are feeling ill (fever, cough, etc) to stay home. We will gladly reschedule your appointment for you when you are feeling better. Also, we are asking the same of our employees, so that you feel as safe as possible when you come to our office.

Here are some helpful tips to stay healthy during this outbreak and cold/flu season: - Avoid touching your face, particularly your eyes, nose, and mouth.
- Wash your hands often and thoroughly.
- Cover your coughs and sneezes.
- If possible, avoid crowded places where infection is more likely to spread

Thank you for making us your provider for foot and ankle care. We look forward to continuing to provide you with the best care possible!

Sincerely,

Dr. Salma Aziz

Hi Everyone! üëã
.
We hope you are doing well and staying healthy!  Due to all of the concerns with the COVID-19 virus our March events are still canceled.  We are sad to not see you all at our different events but hope that changes very soon!
.
That being said, we are taking it all day by day.  With Autism Awareness Month coming very soon in April we would normally have our Business Takeover calendar together and advertising all of the extraordinary businesses that are supporting us this year with a fundraiser.  At this point we don't know what the future looks like for April.  We have not canceled any of the fundraising events at this point in the hopes that we won't need to.  We will be checking in with each and every business to make a plan and see what we can do for the individual events and what to do to help their businesses as much as possible too!  Supporting each other is going to be essential now more than ever.  We're living in a strange time with so many unknowns right now, but know that we will be working together to do what we can for our autism community and our amazing supporters too.
.
We hope that Autism Awareness Month we be full of awareness, acceptance and celebrating each other the way we had pictured, but maybe we'll have May Autism Awareness Month this year! üòâ  Keep an eye out for updates and we'll keep in touch with all of you along the way!
.

.
.
.
.

On the other side , Innocent animals have been cramped in spaces inhospitable, devoid of food , water and hygiene. They‚Äôve died deaths that neither has a reason nor a purpose known to them and some diseased animal instead of given care and love has been slaughtered and put on a dinner plate. Moreover they aren‚Äôt domesticated and Tamed ones, they‚Äôve been smuggled across bordered , abused by their handlers , isolated from their habitats and subjected to everything inhuman. .
.
.
.
.

Nature is just showing a glimpse of how it will be if this continues !! If you are reading this , there is Hope ‚ù§Ô∏è
Both the good and frustrating thing about this : It‚Äôs not permanent. Good because it isn‚Äôt going to last long, bad because we are all being tested to levels we never were !!.
.
.
.
.

Those who are confined to your own private spaces, please don‚Äôt stress eat , it only adds to your state of mind, Listen to music , Dance like crazy , meditate if you can , Get some exercise (there are tons of videos on YouTube on how you can get some while staying indoors). There is light always at the end of the tunnel ! Hold on a little while longer , instead of spreading pandemonium Radiate your positive energy and it will all be over and we can get on with our lives !! If you‚Äôve managed to read this far :
.
.
.

‚Å£
At first we drove out to Danville on one of the few days of the week when it is open. We were stopped by a gate that would not allow us entrance to drive up to where the home is located üôÅ‚Å£
‚Å£
We tried calling‚Äîmany times, with no answer üòû‚Å£
‚Å£
A few days later we finally got through to someone that could give us some information. We ended up making an appointment for a tour which included catching a bus ride up to the site. ‚Å£
‚Å£
I am so glad that we persisted. The tour was fantastic‚ú®‚Äîthe park ranger was extremely knowledgeable‚Äîsharing rich details and information that came to life as we walked through the home, room by room. ‚Å£
‚Å£
I was so intrigued by the story of Eugene‚Äôs life. Full of tragedy and darkness. His home full of symbolism. A man of passion and talent. An extremely curious life. ‚Å£
‚Å£
Please go! I absolutely recommend visiting this harder to get to site. So worth it!‚Å£

insta_description:
Raw Carrot Cake with Vanilla Cashew Frosting ü•ïüç∞ Finally found time to post this super easy and delicious recipe. Make it once - it will become your favorite! üòä‚ù§Ô∏è Recipe:
1 cup walnuts 
1 cup almonds
1/2 cup sunflower seeds 
1 cup pitted dates 
1 cup dried apricots
3 grated medium size carrots 
1 tsp cinnamon 
1/2 tsp ground ginger
Juice from one orange 
For the frosting:
2 cups cashews (soaked in water overnight)
1 tsp vanilla 
1/2 cup coconut milk 
Juice of half a lemon

In a blender throw all of the ingredients and pulse until everything is well combined. Add more orange juice if needed and place the batter in a cake mold. Clean the blender and throw the ingredients for the frosting and blend until you get a smooth and creamy frosting. Place it on top of the batter and freeze it for at least 3 hours.
